<subSubSection id="CCFD0CC3FFF5014963A5F0BE914E8AB7" pageId="23" pageNumber="46" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="84585F48FFF5014963A5F0BE914E8AB7" blockId="23.[151,760,190,405]" pageId="23" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF5014963A5F0BE926A8BF7" bold="true" box="[151,283,190,213]" pageId="23" pageNumber="46">Comments.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF501496214F0BE92BD8BF7" author="MAULIK S." bookContentInfo="xiv + 648 pp. + 1 pl." box="[294,460,190,213]" editor="SEWELL R. B. S." firstAuthor="MAULIK" journalOrPublisher="Taylor and Francis, London" pageId="23" pageNumber="46" refId="ref32093" refString="MAULIK S. 1936: Coleoptera, Chrysomelidae (Galerucinae). In: SEWELL R. B. S. (ed.): The fauna of British India including Ceylon and Burma. Taylor and Francis, London, xiv + 648 pp. + 1 pl." title="Coleoptera, Chrysomelidae (Galerucinae)" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="The fauna of British India including Ceylon and Burma" year="1936">MAULIK (1936)</bibRefCitation>
transferred this species to 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF5014963A5F0DE92788BD7" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1861" box="[151,265,222,245]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Palpoxena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF5014963A5F0DE92788BD7" box="[151,265,222,245]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="46">Palpoxena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and this placement was followed in all subsequent catalogues (
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF501496248F0FE91638A37" author="WILCOX J. A." box="[378,530,254,277]" editor="WILCOX J. A." firstAuthor="WILCOX" journalOrPublisher="Editio seconda. W. Junk, ' s-Gravenhage" pageId="23" pageNumber="46" pagination="433 - 664" refId="ref33616" refString="WILCOX J. A. 1973: Chrysomelidae: Galerucinae: Luperini: Luperina. In: WILCOX J. A. (ed.): Coleopterorum Catalogus Supplementa. Pars 78 (3). Editio seconda. W. Junk, ' s-Gravenhage, pp. 433 - 664." title="Chrysomelidae: Galerucinae: Luperini: Luperina" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Coleopterorum Catalogus Supplementa. Pars 78 (3)." year="1973">WILCOX 1973</bibRefCitation>
, MEDVEDEV &amp; SPRECHER- UEBERSAX 1999, 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF5014962B3F11E917E8A17" author="KIMOTO S." box="[385,527,286,309]" firstAuthor="KIMOTO" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Kitakyushu Museum of Natural History and Human History Series A Natural History" pageId="23" pageNumber="46" pagination="13 - 144" part="3" refId="ref31880" refString="KIMOTO S. 2005: Systematic Catalogue of the Chrysomelidae (Coleoptera) from Nepal and Bhutan. Bulletin of the Kitakyushu Museum of Natural History and Human History Series A Natural History 3: 13 - 144." title="Systematic Catalogue of the Chrysomelidae (Coleoptera) from Nepal and Bhutan" type="journal article" year="2005">KIMOTO 2005</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF50149612AF11E91D68A17" author="BEENEN R." bookContentInfo="924 pp." box="[536,679,286,309]" editor="LOBL I. &amp; SMETANA A." firstAuthor="BEENEN" journalOrPublisher="Apollo Books, Stenstrup" pageId="23" pageNumber="46" pagination="443 - 491" refId="ref30491" refString="BEENEN R. 2010: Galerucinae. Pp. 443 - 491. In: LOBL I. &amp; SMETANA A. (eds.): Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Volume 6. Chrysomeloidea. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, 924 pp." title="Galerucinae." type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Volume 6. Chrysomeloidea" year="2010">BEENEN 2010</bibRefCitation>
). I have found two 
<typeStatus id="5B5CE1EAFFF501496234F13E92138A77" box="[262,354,318,341]" pageId="23" pageNumber="46">syntypes</typeStatus>
(male and female) in BMNH and since the male has the metasternal process I have no doubt to transfer 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF5014963DDF17E92EE8AB7" authorityName="Hope" authorityYear="1831" box="[239,415,382,405]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Auchenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF5014963DDF17E92EE8AB7" box="[239,415,382,405]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="46">Auchenia viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF5014962F3F17E91498AB7" authorityName="Thunberg" authorityYear="1814" box="[449,568,382,405]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Taumacera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF5014962F3F17E91498AB7" box="[449,568,382,405]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="46">Taumacera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
